cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "LLM-PPI-TF-Extraction: LLM-based extraction of protein–protein interactions and transcription factor regulations"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2025-07-01"
authors:
  - family-names: Wiesenbach
    given-names: Philipp
    affiliation: "Dieterich Lab, Heidelberg University Hospital"
    email: philipp.wiesenbach@uni-heidelberg.de
repository-code: "https://github.com/dieterich-lab/LLM-PPI-TF-Extraction"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  A configurable pipeline for extracting molecular interaction triples —
  protein–protein interactions (PPI) and transcription factor–target gene (TF)
  regulations — from biomedical abstracts using large language models.
  Supports multiple extraction strategies including direct extraction,
  NER-then-relation (nerrel), ensemble voting, Tree of Thoughts (ToT), and
  dynamic in-context example retrieval (DynEx), evaluated on the RegulaTome
  benchmark corpus.
keywords:
  - biomedical NLP
  - relation extraction
  - protein-protein interaction
  - transcription factor
  - large language models
  - information extraction
  - RegulaTome
